main event: Multiple UFO sightings in Key West, Florida in July and August 1953 reported by military and civilian observers, including a retired military officer and a student at the U.S. Navy Pre-Flight School.
interesting points: Objects were described as round, white, and hazy in appearance, with estimated speeds of 600 to 800 mph and altitudes of approximately 20,000 to 25,000 feet.
The retired military officer stated that the objects moved at a speed much greater than any known aircraft and were unlike any aircraft he had previously observed.
No official interrogation or identification action was taken, and Air Force control tower records revealed no air traffic in the general area at the times sightings were reported.
The observer's description of the objects corresponded generally with other unidentified sightings reported in the Key West area around that time.
Despite the lack of conclusive evidence, an investigator stated that the observer appeared to be reliable and made the report in good faith.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects described as round, white, and hazy in appearance
witnesses: Military and civilian observers including a retired military officer and a student at the U.S. Navy Pre-Flight School
photographs: No photographs included in the report
